  "original_title": "\u2019\u0b90.\u0b8e\u0bae\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0baa\u0bcd \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'IMF won't help'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Opposition leader Korada Lakshman Kiriyala MP said that until the case investigation filed in the United States of America against the Sri Lankan government is completed, there is a problem in getting assistance from the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Speaking at the press conference held yesterday (07) at the office of the Leader of the Opposition, he said that a case has been filed in the US regarding the bond issue. The names of three Rajapakses have been mentioned in this case and it has been pointed out that the Rajapaksas have kept the looted money as assets in different countries.",
        "Laxman Kriyella also said that there is a problem with the International Monetary Fund providing financial assistance to Sri Lanka until the investigation of this case is completed.",
        "He pointed out that a similar problem has arisen in Venezuela and that the International Monetary Fund has been rejecting them for many years.",
        "Democracy should be ensured in the country. He also said that the American Congress has insisted that the independence of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka should be confirmed.",
        "If we want to get help from the international community, there should be a smooth relationship with the international community, but the government led by President Gotabaya Rajapaksa does not have a smooth relationship with the international community. Especially within 6 months of the inauguration of the President, international countries brought a motion against Sri Lanka in the UN Human Rights Commission. He said that even Islamic countries which normally support Sri Lanka did not support this motion."
      ],
